question: Maya has 11 jars of chocolate chips in her kitchen cabinet. Each jar of chocolate chips can decorate 18 cupcakes. Maya wants to bake enough cupcakes to use up all of her chocolate chips. If each tray holds 6 cupcakes, how many trays worth of cupcakes should she bake?
answer:
She has enough chocolate chips for 11 * 18 = <<11*18=198>>198 cupcakes.
She needs 198 / 6 = <<198/6=33>>33 trays to bake all of the cupcakes.
#### 33
